    "description": "Rix Corporation manufactures and sells machinery and equipment, measuring instruments, and consumables for steel, automobiles, electronics, semiconductors, rubber and tires, machine tools, environment, pulp and paper, ship building, medicine, high-function materials, and food industries in Japan. The company provides rotary; rocky insulator; Nitte lights; lubricants under FRICTTLE name; hardlock nuts, bearing nuts, and set screw; and oil seals, O-rings, iron rubbers, mechanical seals, welded bellows, flexible circuits, etc. It also offers Auto Flush, a system that reduces leakage; oil skimmers; and vivid screen. In addition, the company engages in the construction, manufacturing, and sale of pipes and steel structures, as well as bearing regeneration, new bearing and part manufacturing, precision grinding, polishing, universal joint repair, and related equipment sales; manufacture, sale, and maintenance of automobile parts cleaning equipment and other industrial machinery; import and sale of anti-rust agents, moisture inhibitors, and adhesives; and coolant automatic dilution device manufacturing, electrical and control software design, control panel manufacturing and wiring work, and robot control. Further, it provides phenolic resin molded products; FRP corrosion-resistant pumps, fans, dampers, strainers, and scrubbers; washing machines for automobile parts and semiconductor; and jigs and tools, FPD manufacturing equipment, electronic and optical component manufacturing equipment, consumable parts, dry vacuum pumps, air compressors, valves for tire curing presses, tire manufacturing equipment, and hydraulic equipment. Additionally, the company is involved in the sale and repair of vacuum equipment; maintenance and management services for semiconductor manufacturing equipment; and design, manufacture, assembly, and maintenance of processed products and overhaul of machine tools. Rix Corporation was founded in 1907 and is headquartered in Fukuoka 